nts2.n: AGE OF CONCORD AND REPOSE W/ ALONSO FLORES
nts2.d: Stillness drifts as tenderness echoes and aches; songs for quiet reflection and unanchored listening, live from Copenhagen.
Home is peace — an ambient journey through migration, memory, and return. A sound collection of shared memories and distant places, like an albatross crossing the sea, finding calm in echoes of home

It’s beautiful to feel how everything is connected.
You just have to listen closely,
and you can hear how the eternal thread stretches on,
binding everything together — you, me, Lonnie Holley and Alice Coltrane. Join me on this trip to inner peace.

nts2.n: Waves of Peace w/ Jaxx TMS
nts2.d: For this mix I chose a selection that takes me to a place of peace, a state where im not thinking, just being.Everything else fades away. You are fully present, almost meditative. I wanted to create a space to breathe, listen and float. Sounds that move through us so we can be carried by their melodies. Creating this felt completely naturally, almost effortlessly, it resonates so deeply with me to my own stillness.

My dad has always played the guitar, and this collection of music revolves around his favorite instrument. From classic folk tales to droning harmonics, I trace the path of finding one's own self-sustainment and peace of mind through sonic meditation.
Image: untitled drawing by my dad, 1974.

i feel most at peace when i’m outside, taking in the beauty of nature and things around me. this mix channels that feeling of inner peace - so grab your headphones and go outside!
may we all be able to experience this feeling <3

nts2.d: RADIO SUPER is Rosa Pistola’s show on NTS where she dives deep into the Latin American underground. Each episode zooms into different genres, scenes, and vibes, tracing their roots and evolution. It’s all about the sounds, the stories, and the pillars of the underground.

nts2.d: Mexican record label, Naafi, settle in at NTS for a showcase of the weirdest experimentations in club culture that have bubbled to the surface of Soundcloud. Dazed rhythms converging into Jersey stutters, and tumblr-era trap for two straight hours on a Monday.
DJ, Run Dem Crew Founder, and community builder Charlie Dark MBE spins gems from his record collection once a month.

Carolina Soul is a record seller based in Durham, NC, USA. They specialize in rare and classic soul, boogie, gospel and modern obscure tracks from the Carolinas and beyond, mixed with all-time bangers and ballads.

nts2.n: WEAPONISE YOUR SOUND W/ DIET CLINIC

subtle.d: Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.
Hailing from Belfast but making moves in Nottingham, Nikki O is a DJ and radio presenter whose sets blend 4/4 rhythms, breakbeats, and the bassier side of techno.
